form_values.2d29:
Densest Himalayan balsam growth was noted within areas where soil movement has occurred previously (centre-west side). Generally growth is now very thinly distributed. Growth noted further into south-west corner than previously.
The catchment area survey identified no other Himalayan balsam infestations within 500 metres east or west of the site and 1000 metres north or south of the site. Although direct access to the entirety of the land within the catchment survey area was not possible and views of some areas of land were restricted, additional studies of aerial imagery of the catchment area reveal land use types and topography that does not favour Himalayan balsam, including the lack of any surface water bodies.
Taking the above into account, along with the presence of stockpiles of soil and stone on site, the conclusion drawn is that the Himalayan balsam infestation on site is due to the import into site in the past of material containing Himalayan balsam seed.
